  "- **Dashboard**: View all your MailChimp lists with subscriber statistics\n- **List Maintenance**: Identify people in MailChimp but not in CRM, and vice versa\n- **Contact Integration**: View MailChimp subscription status on Person and Family pages\n- **Automatic Sync**: Hooks into person/family updates to keep MailChimp in sync": "",
  "1. Create a Vonage account at https://dashboard.nexmo.com/sign-up (new accounts include free trial credit)\n2. Find your API Key and API Secret on the Vonage Dashboard homepage\n3. Go to Numbers > Buy Numbers and purchase a number with SMS capability\n4. Note the number in E.164 format (e.g., +14155551234)\n5. In ChurchCRM, enable the Vonage SMS plugin and enter your credentials": "",
  "1. Go to Google Analytics (analytics.google.com)\n2. Create a property or select an existing one\n3. Go to Admin → Data Streams → Web\n4. Copy the Measurement ID (starts with G-)": "",
  "1. Install OpenLP 3.0 or later on your presentation computer\n2. Enable the Remote plugin in OpenLP (Settings → Configure OpenLP → Plugins)\n3. Enable the Alerts plugin in OpenLP for alert display support\n4. Note the IP address of the OpenLP computer\n5. Enter the server URL in the format: http://IP_ADDRESS:4316\n6. If you've configured authentication in OpenLP, enter the username and password": "",
  "Access the MailChimp Dashboard from the Email menu. The dashboard shows:\n\n- Member count for each list\n- Campaign statistics\n- Unsubscribe counts\n- List maintenance tools": "",
  "Adding Links": "Προσθήκη Συνδέσμων",
